Issues.Body:
**What version of Tailwind CSS are you using?**

Version 3.1.5 and Postcss v8.4.14

**What build tool (or framework if it abstracts the build tool) are you using?**

Vite v2.9.9 | create-react-app v5.0.1

**What version of Node.js are you using?**

v16.13.1

**What browser are you using?**

Chrome (103.0.5060.114) and Firefox Developer Edition (103.0b6)

**What operating system are you using?**

Windows

**Reproduction URL**
No need. The configuration is the default one.

index.css
```css
 @tailwind base;
 @tailwind components;
 @tailwind utilities;
```

tailwind.config.js
```js
  /** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  content: [
    "./src/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

postcss.config.js
```js
module.exports = {
  plugins: {
    tailwindcss: {},
    autoprefixer: {},
  },
}
```

**Describe your issue**
While using Tailwind CSS, every HTML **dialog** element is always visible, even when the _open_ attribute is not present. If I comment the **@tailwind utilities** line on my index.css file it works as expected but then Tailwind becomes disabled.
Tried this with Vite, create-react-app and a vanilla html and CSS project. The inclusion of tailwind directives modifies the expected behavior of a dialog element upon being rendered.
